metadata.name: Survive in Virtuality (HKG)
metadata.description:
The city is a lonely place 

Where scary shadows dance in space 


The only solace he can find 

Is in the virtual world of his mind 


He wanders through the neon lights 

And wonders why he fights this plight 


He belongs here, yet he feels so far 

So he takes refuge in a virtual bar 


No one knows his secrets there 

No judgment, no stares, noone cares 



He's free to be who he wants to be 

In this world, he's truly free 


Away from the world of reality 

To a place that's full of fantasy 


Where he can forget his pain and strife 

And find comfort in his virtual life
